JPMorgan Chase & Co And Others Face US Lawsuit-Reuters
Wednesday, 7 Aug 2013 03:01pm EDT
Reuters reported that Glencore Xstrata PLC and JPMorgan Chase & Co face a U.S. lawsuit alleging they artificially inflated aluminum prices and disrupted supplies. The suit, filed in a district court in Florida on August 6, 2013 also named Goldman Sachs Group Inc, The London Metal Exchange (LME) and subsidiaries of both JPMorgan and Goldman and accused the companies of antitrust practices and racketeering. All three seek class action status. Allegations center on Goldman and its warehouse company Metro, which plaintiffs accuse of violating antitrust laws by restraining supplies and inflating aluminum prices. The companies could face fines if the lawsuits are successful.Â 
